1. Install NEURON 9.0.1 
  a. The NEURON Simulator — NEURON documentation 
  b. Go into your files, rename the “Unconfirmed Download” to have the .exe suffix (yes, this is safe), and run. 
2. Get your Python environment to recognize this installation 
  a. Check where your new nrn file is located. Most likely C:/nrn. Save this path. 
  b. Go into C:/Users/YOUR_ACCOUNT_NAME/miniconda3/site-packages. 
  c. Create a new .txt file. Paste the directory you copied into there, and then add /lib/python. For example, if my nrn folder is at C:/nrn, I’ll paste C:/nrn/Lib/python. This should be the only text in the text file. 
  d. Rename this file to neuron.pth. The suffix must be changed to path; not neuron.pth.txt. 
3. Test if the package works 
  a. Open up a python folder and run the following code. If this works, then you can now use NEURON. If this errors, contact Jack Kidnie in class or at jlkhg8 for assistance. 
    i. Import neuron 
    ii. Neuron.test()
